Subject: Public Swim Drop-In (All Ages) | Century Gardens 1:00-2:00pm
Description: Open to participants of all ages and swimming abilities.    AQUATIC ADMISSION STANDARDS APPLY: All swim participants 5 years of age or younger must be directly supervised by a parent/guardian who is at least 14 years of age.  Swim participants between 6 and 9 years of age who are able to pass the Facility Swim Test must be accompanied by a parent/guardian who is at 14 years of age.  Swim participants between 6 and nine 9 years of age who are unable to pass the Facility Swim Test must be directly supervised by a parent/guardian who is at least 14 years of age.  Please see www.brampton.ca/recreation for more information.
RegistrationNotes: Aquatic Admission Standards: All swim participants five (5) years of age or younger must be directly supervised by a parent/guardian who is at least fourteen (14) years of age. The parent/guardian must be in the water wearing bathing attire, within arm's reach of the swimmer, and able to render immediate assistance if necessary. Subject: Public Swim Drop-In (All Ages) | Chinguacousy Wellness Centre 1:00-2:00pm
Description: Open to participants of all ages and swimming abilities.    AQUATIC ADMISSION STANDARDS APPLY: All swim participants 5 years of age or younger must be directly supervised by a parent/guardian who is at least 14 years of age.  Swim participants between 6 and 9 years of age who are able to pass the Facility Swim Test must be accompanied by a parent/guardian who is at 14 years of age.  Swim participants between 6 and nine 9 years of age who are unable to pass the Facility Swim Test must be directly supervised by a parent/guardian who is at least 14 years of age.  Please see www.brampton.ca/recreation for more information.
RegistrationNotes: Aquatic Admission Standards: All swim participants five (5) years of age or younger must be directly supervised by a parent/guardian who is at least fourteen (14) years of age. The parent/guardian must be in the water wearing bathing attire, within arm's reach of the swimmer, and able to render immediate assistance if necessary. Swim participants between six (6) and nine (9) years of age who are able to pass the Facility Swim Test must be accompanied by a parent/guardian who is at least fourteen (14) years of age. The parent/guardian must maintain visual contact with the participant and remain within the pool enclosure at all times. Swim participants between six (6) and nine (9) years of age who are unable to pass the Facility Swim Test must be directly supervised by a parent/guardian who is at least fourteen (14) years of age. The parent/guardian must be in the water wearing bathing attire, within arm's reach of the swimmer, and able to render immediate assistance if necessary. One parent/guardian may assume responsibility for up to two (2) swimmers requiring direct supervision or up to eight (8) swimmers requiring direct supervision if all children are wearing a Personal Floatation Device (PFD).

Subject: Figure Skating Drop-In ( 6+ Years) | Cassie Campbell 3:00-3:50pm
Description: For experienced figure skaters to individually practice their spins, jumps and the fundamentals of figure skating. Everyone with skates must pay to attend. This program is unsupervised during non-prime hours. Skating admission guidelines must be followed. Those under 10 years of age must be supervised by a parent/guardian 14 years of age or older.  Prerequisites: All skaters must have good control/balance when skating forward, backward and be excellent at stopping, as well as maneuvering around obstacles on the ice.  Restrictions: No lifts are allowed. No synchronized team practice, though individuals can practice routines individually. Music will not be played for the consideration of everyone attending. Jump harnesses will not be permitted for use.   Recommended: It is highly recommended that all participants come with a parent/guardian or coach, consider wearing a Canadian Standard Association (CSA) certified hockey helmet, and be at Skate Canada STAR 1 level or higher. Subject: Public Swim Drop-In (55+ Years) | Susan Fennell Sportsplex 8:30-9:30am
Description: Open to participants 55 years of age or older of all swimming abilities.
SetupInstruction: Open to participants 55 years of age or older of all swimming abilities.
RegistrationNotes: Aquatic Admission Standards: All swim participants five (5) years of age or younger must be directly supervised by a parent/guardian who is at least fourteen (14) years of age. The parent/guardian must be in the water wearing bathing attire, within arm's reach of the swimmer, and able to render immediate assistance if necessary. Swim participants between six (6) and nine (9) years of age who are able to pass the Facility Swim Test must be accompanied by a parent/guardian who is at least fourteen (14) years of age. The parent/guardian must maintain visual contact with the participant and remain within the pool enclosure at all times. Swim participants between six (6) and nine (9) years of age who are unable to pass the Facility Swim Test must be directly supervised by a parent/guardian who is at least fourteen (14) years of age. The parent/guardian must be in the water wearing bathing attire, within arm's reach of the swimmer, and able to render immediate assistance if necessary. One parent/guardian may assume responsibility for up to two (2) swimmers requiring direct supervision or up to eight (8) swimmers requiring direct supervision if all children are wearing a Personal Floatation Device (PFD).

RegistrationNotes: Aquatic Admission Standards: All swim participants five (5) years of age or younger must be directly supervised by a parent/guardian who is at least fourteen (14) years of age. The parent/guardian must be in the water wearing bathing attire, within arm's reach of the swimmer, and able to render immediate assistance if necessary. Swim participants between six (6) and nine (9) years of age who are unable to pass the Facility Swim Test must be directly supervised by a parent/guardian who is at least fourteen (14) years of age. One parent/guardian may assume responsibility for up to two (2) swimmers requiring direct supervision or up to eight (8) swimmers requiring direct supervision if all children are wearing a Personal Floatation Device (PFD).

Subject: Public Swim Drop-In (All Ages) | Chinguacousy Wellness Centre 7:40-8:40pm
Description: Open to participants of all ages and swimming abilities.    AQUATIC ADMISSION STANDARDS APPLY: All swim participants 5 years of age or younger must be directly supervised by a parent/guardian who is at least 14 years of age.  Swim participants between 6 and 9 years of age who are able to pass the Facility Swim Test must be accompanied by a parent/guardian who is at 14 years of age.  Swim participants between 6 and nine 9 years of age who are unable to pass the Facility Swim Test must be directly supervised by a parent/guardian who is at least 14 years of age.  Please see www.brampton.ca/recreation for more information.
RegistrationNotes: Aquatic Admission Standards: All swim participants five (5) years of age or younger must be directly supervised by a parent/guardian who is at least fourteen (14) years of age. The parent/guardian must be in the water wearing bathing attire, within arm's reach of the swimmer, and able to render immediate assistance if necessary. Swim participants between six (6) and nine (9) years of age who are able to pass the Facility Swim Test must be accompanied by a parent/guardian who is at least fourteen (14) years of age. The parent/guardian must maintain visual contact with the participant and remain within the pool enclosure at all times. Swim participants between six (6) and nine (9) years of age who are unable to pass the Facility Swim Test must be directly supervised by a parent/guardian who is at least fourteen (14) years of age. The parent/guardian must be in the water wearing bathing attire, within arm's reach of the swimmer, and able to render immediate assistance if necessary. One parent/guardian may assume responsibility for up to two (2) swimmers requiring direct supervision or up to eight (8) swimmers requiring direct supervision if all children are wearing a Personal Floatation Device (PFD).

Subject: Figure Skating Drop-In ( 6+ Years) | Cassie Campbell 6:30-8:20am
Description: For experienced figure skaters to individually practice their spins, jumps and the fundamentals of figure skating. Everyone with skates must pay to attend. This program is unsupervised during non-prime hours. Skating admission guidelines must be followed. Those under 10 years of age must be supervised by a parent/guardian 14 years of age or older.  Prerequisites: All skaters must have good control/balance when skating forward, backward and be excellent at stopping, as well as maneuvering around obstacles on the ice.  Restrictions: No lifts are allowed. No synchronized team practice, though individuals can practice routines individually. Music will not be played for the consideration of everyone attending. Jump harnesses will not be permitted for use.   Recommended: It is highly recommended that all participants come with a parent/guardian or coach, consider wearing a Canadian Standard Association (CSA) certified hockey helmet, and be at Skate Canada STAR 1 level or higher.   This program is not scheduled to run on Sept. 2nd, Oct. 14th, Nov. 29th, Dec. 25th, Jan. 1st, Feb. 7th  Feb 17th, Apr. 18th, Apr. 21st, May. 19th, Aug. 4th.

Subject: Public Swim Parent and Child Drop-In (10 Years and Under) | Ellen Mitchell 10:00-11:00am
Description: Open to children 10 years of age and under accompanied by a parent/guardian 14 years of age or older in the water.    AQUATIC ADMISSION STANDARDS APPLY: All swim participants 5 years of age or younger must be directly supervised by a parent/guardian who is at least 14 years of age.  Swim participants between 6 and 9 years of age who are able to pass the Facility Swim Test must be accompanied by a parent/guardian who is at 14 years of age.  Swim participants between 6 and nine 9 years of age who are unable to pass the Facility Swim Test must be directly supervised by a parent/guardian who is at least 14 years of age.  Please see www.brampton.ca/recreation for more information.
RegistrationNotes: Aquatic Admission Standards: All swim participants five (5) years of age or younger must be directly supervised by a parent/guardian who is at least fourteen (14) years of age. The parent/guardian must be in the water wearing bathing attire, within arm's reach of the swimmer, and able to render immediate assistance if necessary. Swim participants between six (6) and nine (9) years of age who are able to pass the Facility Swim Test must be accompanied by a parent/guardian who is at least fourteen (14) years of age. The parent/guardian must maintain visual contact with the participant and remain within the pool enclosure at all times. Swim participants between six (6) and nine (9) years of age who are unable to pass the Facility Swim Test must be directly supervised by a parent/guardian who is at least fourteen (14) years of age. The parent/guardian must be in the water wearing bathing attire, within arm's reach of the swimmer, and able to render immediate assistance if necessary. One parent/guardian may assume responsibility for up to two (2) swimmers requiring direct supervision or up to eight (8) swimmers requiring direct supervision if all children are wearing a Personal Floatation Device (PFD).

Subject: Adult Swim Drop-In (18+ Years) | Century Gardens  12:00-1:0pm
Description: Open to participants 18 years of age or older of all swimming abilities
Days: Every Mon, Tue, Wed, Thu, Fri
RegistrationNotes: Aquatic Admission Standards: All swim participants five (5) years of age or younger must be directly supervised by a parent/guardian who is at least fourteen (14) years of age. The parent/guardian must be in the water wearing bathing attire, within arm's reach of the swimmer, and able to render immediate assistance if necessary. Swim participants between six (6) and nine (9) years of age who are able to pass the Facility Swim Test must be accompanied by a parent/guardian who is at least fourteen (14) years of age. The parent/guardian must maintain visual contact with the participant and remain within the pool enclosure at all times. Swim participants between six (6) and nine (9) years of age who are unable to pass the Facility Swim Test must be directly supervised by a parent/guardian who is at least fourteen (14) years of age. The parent/guardian must be in the water wearing bathing attire, within arm's reach of the swimmer, and able to render immediate assistance if necessary. One parent/guardian may assume responsibility for up to two (2) swimmers requiring direct supervision or up to eight (8) swimmers requiring direct supervision if all children are wearing a Personal Floatation Device (PFD).
